    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so you're saying it was a success because Gaddafi is gone, even though it led to chaos? doesn't that kind of make any intervention that causes long-term instability an inherent failure in the end? wouldn't a realist argue that the destabilization of a major regional player is a net loss for global security?",
