    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that kind of a circular argument though? you're saying the intervention was a \"win\" but the outcome was chaos and extremism. if the goal of any foreign policy is to increase security, and this actually decreased it, how can you call the act itself a success? it feels like you're trying to justify the intervention by saying it just wasn't \"done right,\" instead of admitting the premise of regime change itself might be a flawed strategic tool.",
